{"id":2273,"date":"2020-11-13T16:54:20","date_gmt":"2020-11-13T16:54:20","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/nuckles.rtrk.us\/?page_id=2273"},"modified":"2022-12-14T17:12:13","modified_gmt":"2022-12-14T17:12:13","slug":"home","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/ostif.org\/","title":{"rendered":"Home"},"content":{"rendered":"<header class=\"page-header centered-page-header\" style=\"background-image: url('http:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/banner-homepage.svg'); padding: 112px 30px;\">\n<div class=\"container clr page-header-inner\">\n<h1 class=\"page-header-title clr\">Open Source Technology <span class=\"clause\">Improvement Fund<\/span><\/h1>\n<div class=\"clr page-subheading\">Securing Open Source for the World<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/header>\n<div class=\"content-row\">\n<div class=\"oceanwp-row clr\">\n<div class=\"span_1_of_1 col col-1 clr\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Open Source Technology Improvement Fund is a corporate non-profit dedicated to <strong>securing open source apps<\/strong> that we all depend on. Securing software isn&#8217;t easy, and we know what it takes to succeed. By facilitating security audits and reviews, OSTIF makes it easy for projects to significantly improve security.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-row\">\n<div class=\"oceanwp-row clr\">\n<div class=\"span_1_of_1 col col-1 clr\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Better Security Through A Massive Community<\/h2>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-2764\" src=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/LOGOWALL-AWSADD-1024x537.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"537\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/LOGOWALL-AWSADD-1024x537.png 1024w, https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/LOGOWALL-AWSADD-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/LOGOWALL-AWSADD-768x402.png 768w, https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/LOGOWALL-AWSADD-1536x805.png 1536w, https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/LOGOWALL-AWSADD-2048x1073.png 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Through the Open Source Technology Improvement Fund, projects have been able to <strong>find and fix<\/strong> critical security bugs.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"span_1_of_5 col col-1 clr\">\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"margin: 20px auto 10px; display: block;\" src=\"http:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/icon-projects.svg\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 32px;\">22+<\/span><br \/>\npartner projects<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"span_1_of_5 col clr\">\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"margin: 20px auto 10px; display: block;\" src=\"http:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/icon-sponsors.svg\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 32px;\">1000+<\/span><br \/>\nworld class security experts<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"span_1_of_5 col clr\">\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"margin: 20px auto 10px; display: block;\" src=\"http:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/icon-audits.svg\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 32px;\">5000+<\/span><br \/>\nhours of security review<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"span_1_of_5 col clr\">\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"margin: 20px auto 10px; display: block;\" src=\"http:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/icon-bug.svg\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 32px;\">50+<\/span><br \/>\nsevere bugs patched<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"span_1_of_5 col clr\">\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"margin: 20px auto 10px; display: block;\" src=\"http:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/icon-shield.svg\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 32px;\">billions<\/span><br \/>\nprotected<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-row\" style=\"background-color: #efefef;\">\n<div class=\"oceanwp-row clr\">\n<div class=\"span_1_of_1 col col-1 clr\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Support the OSTIF Mission<\/h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Open-source projects keep today&#8217;s Internet infrastructure afloat. They are critical for the operation of every webserver, every browser, and every banking platform. And they are cared for by a <strong>surprisingly small<\/strong> group of people with a limited amount of time. Without dedicated security experts, these projects often don&#8217;t get the attention they require.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>We can do it with help from supporters like you.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a class=\"button\" href=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/sponsorship\">Become a Sponsor<\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-row\"><div class=\"latestnews\"><div class=\"listing-item\"><a class=\"image\" href=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/dapr-audit\/\"><img width=\"200\" height=\"200\" src=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/daprlogo.png\" class=\"attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/daprlogo.png 200w, https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/daprlogo-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" \/><\/a> <a class=\"title\" href=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/dapr-audit\/\">Dampening Vulnerabilities in Dapr: Security Audit of Dapr<\/a> <span class=\"excerpt\">In May and June of 2023, OSTIF and ADA Logics worked with the open source project Dapr on a holistic security audit. The Distributed Application Runtime (or Dapr) is a&hellip; <a class=\"excerpt-more\" href=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/dapr-audit\/\">Read more \u00bb<\/a><\/span><\/div><div class=\"listing-item\"><a class=\"image\" href=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/envoy-security-audit\/\"><img width=\"300\" height=\"70\" src=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/envoylogo2-e1692024459431-300x70.png\" class=\"attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/envoylogo2-e1692024459431-300x70.png 300w, https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/envoylogo2-e1692024459431-1024x241.png 1024w, https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/envoylogo2-e1692024459431-768x180.png 768w, https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/envoylogo2-e1692024459431.png 1115w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a> <a class=\"title\" href=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/envoy-security-audit\/\">OSTIF collaborates with the Envoy Team to further improve security posture.<\/a> <span class=\"excerpt\">Envoy, the open source edge and service proxy designed for cloud-native applications, worked with OSTIF and X41 D-Sec to help improve the project\u2019s security posture. The multi-phased engagement, sponsored by&hellip; <a class=\"excerpt-more\" href=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/envoy-security-audit\/\">Read more \u00bb<\/a><\/span><\/div><div class=\"listing-item\"><a class=\"image\" href=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/crossplane-audit-complete\/\"><img width=\"217\" height=\"233\" src=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/crossplanelogo.png\" class=\"attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" \/><\/a> <a class=\"title\" href=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/crossplane-audit-complete\/\">OSTIF completes Security Audit of Crossplane- improved across the board!<\/a> <span class=\"excerpt\">Crossplane underwent a successful third party security audit by ADA Logics with the support of Open Source Technology Improvement Fund (OSTIF). Used by firms such as JP Morgan, Time Warner,&hellip; <a class=\"excerpt-more\" href=\"https:\/\/ostif.org\/crossplane-audit-complete\/\">Read more \u00bb<\/a><\/span><\/div><\/div><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Open Source Technology Improvement Fund Securing Open Source for the World The Open Source Technology Improvement Fund is a corporate non-profit dedicated to securing open source apps that we all depend on. Securing software isn&#8217;t easy, and we know what it takes to succeed. By facilitating security audits and reviews, OSTIF makes it easy for [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/2273"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2273"}],"version-history":[{"count":93,"href":"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/2273\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2765,"href":"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/2273\/revisions\/2765"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/ostif.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=2273"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}